Enumeration Type Documentation

enum dec_flags_e

decoder flags

Enumerator:
DEC_DECODE_SEI  This flag will tell decoder to decode sei-messages Application can access to it via sei-list, attached to the output frame If this flag is not set, sei messages are attached to frame "as is", without separating and decoding.
DEC_INTERP_PIC_STRUCT  This flag controls how decoder will deal with pic_struct received by timing SEI.

if this flag is 0 nothing is done. if this flag is 1 decoder interpret this parameter inside. I.e. make telecine and other actions.

DEC_POST_DEBLOCK  enable "postprocessing" deblocking when "inloop" deblocking is disabled
DEC_FULL_ERR_CONC  enable full error concealment for lost data;
DEC_BOTTOM_FIELD_FIRST  output bottom field first (effective only when DEC_INTERP_PIC_STRUCT is set);
DEC_ANALYSE_ONLY  this flag disable actual frames decoding.

Used for stream analysing If opened with this flag, decoder will not produce output frames. It also will not handle NAL samples release. Caller must handle it itself.

DEC_SKIP_NON_REF_DEBLOCKING  this flag force decoder to skip deblocking for nonreference pictures can be used for decoder speedup
DEC_SKIP_REF_DEBLOCKING  this flag force decoder to skip deblocking for reference pictures can be used for decoder speedup
DEC_DISABLE_FMO  this flag force decoder to skip decoding of pictures, coded using FMO
DEC_INTERP_FRAME_PACKING_SEI  this flag force decoder to depack frame accoriding to frame packing sei-message
